{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2021/minimal-technical-blogging-part4/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"gatsby-minimal-simple-blog","lang":"en"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7196c6ae-4666-5999-909d-df9fb74fa9a6","excerpt":"Photo by Daniel Thomas on Unsplash In the last article in the serie, I have introduced you to my minimal blogging setup using Gatsby and Github Pages: Using…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#what-is-a-starter-library\">What is a starter library?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#what-included\">What included?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#how-to-use\">How to use?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#future-development\">Future development</a></li>\n</ul>","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/9451d/banner.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 76.58227848101265%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"writing blog\"\n        title=\"writing blog\"\n        src=\"/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/f058b/banner.png\"\n        srcset=\"/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/c26ae/banner.png 158w,\n/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/6bdcf/banner.png 315w,\n/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/f058b/banner.png 630w,\n/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/40601/banner.png 945w,\n/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/78612/banner.png 1260w,\n/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog/static/c82500264fe0a761984aedb4c0253f69/9451d/banner.png 2782w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><sub>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@dtbosse\">Daniel Thomas</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/blogging\">Unsplash</a><sub></p>\n<p>In the <a href=\"https://antran.app/2021/minimal-technical-blogging-part3/\">last article</a> in the serie, I have introduced you to my minimal blogging setup using Gatsby and Github Pages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Using <strong>Gatsby</strong> as static site generator, we can easily create a static site for our Markdown content. The generated site is highly customizable, easily extensible and fast.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Using <strong>Github Pages</strong>, we can host the generated site for FREE on Github infrastructure</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Using <strong>Github Actions</strong> automation, we can deploy our site automatically from Github. With Renovate bot integration, we keep dependencies up-to-date automatically as well</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In this article, I’ll introduce you to the <a href=\"https://github.com/antranapp/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog\">gatsby-minimal-simple-blog</a> package, which is the bare-bone package containing all customizations I have for my blog.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-starter-library\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-is-a-starter-library\" aria-label=\"what is a starter library permalink\" class=\"autolink-heading before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is a starter library?</h2>\n<p>A starter library is a basic boilerplate package to kick start a Gatsby projoct.</p>\n<p>When you first install Gatsbyjs, you normally install the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-blog\">gatsby-blog-starter</a> to have a bare-bone template for your project.</p>\n<p>There are <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/starters/\">many other starter libaries</a> available, containing different set of customizations, and suitable for different purpose.</p>\n<p>To enable other people to be able to create a similar blogging site as mine, I have extract all customizations I have for my blog into the <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-minimal-simple-blog</code> package. Everyone can easily use this library to kick off a new project wit this template. This starter ships with all customizations I have for <a href=\"https://antran.app\">my blog</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"what-included\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-included\" aria-label=\"what included permalink\" class=\"autolink-heading before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What included?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Blazing fast, minimal template</li>\n<li>Design inspired by <a href=\"https://overreacted.io\">Overreacted.io</a></li>\n<li>Support for an RSS feed</li>\n<li>Automatic optimization of images in Markdown posts</li>\n<li>Support for code syntax highlighting</li>\n<li>Includes plugins for easy, beautiful typography</li>\n<li>Includes React Helmet to allow editing site meta tags</li>\n<li>Includes plugins for offline support out of the box</li>\n<li>Table of content</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-label=\"how to use permalink\" class=\"autolink-heading before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use?</h2>\n<p>Just follow the <code class=\"language-text\">README.md</code> in <a href=\"https://github.com/antranapp/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog\">the project repository</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"future-development\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#future-development\" aria-label=\"future development permalink\" class=\"autolink-heading before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Future development</h2>\n<p>I want to keep this starter as minimal as possible. But if you have and ideas to improve the template, feel free to open issues, pull requests at <a href=\"https://github.com/antranapp/gatsby-minimal-simple-blog\">the repository</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Starting a technical blog in 2021 - Minimal starter package (Part 4)","date":"April 14, 2021","description":"How to start a minimal blog using the gatsby-minimal-simple-blog package?","tags":["react","gatsby","blogging"],"toc":null},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"},"langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2021/minimal-technical-blogging-part4/","previous":{"id":"c261722c-3e87-5d00-ab89-0787d4a76d42","fields":{"slug":"/2021/minimal-technical-blogging-part3/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"2021/minimal-technical-blogging-part3"},"frontmatter":{"date":"April 12, 2021","title":"Starting a technical blog in 2021 - Gatsby + Github Pages (Part 3)","tags":["react","gatsby","blogging"]}},"next":null,"translationsLink":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3257411868"]}